ssary. I believe the dependencies are already resolved transitively. I should consider if I need to require bcpkix and bcprov deterministically. The generated scaffold includes the target library with testImplementation, so I may only need an extra Maven dependency if it’s optional or test scoped. It looks like the POM declares BouncyCastle compile dependencies, so no extra action is needed.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra setup is required: io.netty:netty-pkitesting already brings its runtime dependencies transitively and its normal use is in-process certificate/CRL test utility code using JDK APIs, BouncyCastle, and a loopback HttpServer.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The current failing test exercises the ML-DSA path with a hand-written fake key; that path reflectively loads java.security.AsymmetricKey and is sensitive to the actual JDK API level. This is a test-design/JDK-compatibility concern, not an external setup requirement.\",\n    \"RevocationServer starts a local loopback HTTP server on a random port; this should not require Docker, but native-image/JVM tests may need to avoid assuming a fixed port or external network access.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_07dc714a6fcb5c92016a3eac875bb48193a4133bd3d8ebb5d9\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 6164, "output": 712, "cacheRead": 22016, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 28892, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782492282431, "responseId": "resp_07dc714a6fcb5c92016a3eac7ae3f48193b7080a1bf51832cf"}, "toolResults": []}
